The paper discusses the design and implementation of a new collective protocol for network interfaces to offload communication processing from host CPUs, specifically for barrier operations. This falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also focuses on the use of network interfaces (NICs) for efficient communication, which falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses performance evaluation and analytical modeling, which could fall under Performance (cs.PF), Architecture (cs.AR), and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
